The paper deals with the complexity of problems related to finding the Kth largest subset and Kth largest m-tuple, which are combinatorial optimization problems. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.CGT (Combinatorics and Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the complexity of problems related to information theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves reductions from NP-hard problems, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
